\paragraph{Status of the Okamoto null-sum constraint.}
Under the WLOG fixing $\eta_\infty = \eta_0 = 1$, Okamoto's
classical $P_{III}$ ODE coefficients are
\cite[eq.~(0.1)]{okamoto1987painleveIII}:
\[
\alpha_{\mathrm{ODE}} = -4 \theta_\infty,
\qquad
\beta_{\mathrm{ODE}} = 4(\theta_0 + 1),
\qquad
\gamma_{\mathrm{ODE}} = 4,
\qquad
\delta_{\mathrm{ODE}} = -4.
\]
These are not the project 4-tuple. The project 4-tuple satisfies
the Okamoto monodromy-data constraint
$\alpha_\infty + \alpha_0 + \beta_\infty + \beta_0 = 0$
% [TBD: verify whether this null-sum constraint is in fact
%       Okamoto's, or whether it is a project assumption from
%       058R \S B.3. The constraint is stated in 058R but no
%       primary-literature cite was given there.]
\emph{except} at the V$_\mathrm{quad}$ parameter point
$(1/6, 0, 0, -1/2)$, where the null-sum equals $-1/3$.
This $-1/3$ offset has been carried as an open anomaly since
the 2026-05-02 V$_\mathrm{quad}$/$P_{III}(D_6)$
normalisation-map session
% [bridge-internal cite: 058R phase_b_canonical_map.md \S B.3
%  anomaly D2; not part of the public v1.3 record. If this
%  paragraph is to land in CT v1.3 \emph{public} text, replace
%  with a primary-literature cite.]
and is plausibly attributed to one of the following mechanisms.
\begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph*)]
\item \emph{Hamiltonian expansion residual.} The KNY 2017 \S 8.5.17
  Hamiltonian \cite[eq.~8.237]{kajiwaranoumiyamada2017} differs
  from Okamoto's $H_{III}$ by a $t$-linear correction; under
  pull-back to the V$_\mathrm{quad}$ parameter point this
  produces a $-1/3$ shift in the null-sum.
\item \emph{Additive-shift component of the rename.} The four
  rename equations include constant shifts
  $c_\infty + c_0 + d_\infty + d_0 = -1/3$.
\item \emph{Sakai surface-type artefact.} The $D_6$ surface
  geometry of $P_{III}(D_6)$ \cite{sakai1999preprint,
  kajiwaranoumiyamada2017} forces a fixed off-set in the
  monodromy-parameter chart that is invisible in the
  Hamiltonian formulation.
\end{enumerate}
At v1.3 the project adopts the $-1/3$ offset as a
\emph{named acceptance criterion} for any future closure
attempt of the M6.CC R1 chart-map: any candidate map
$(a_n, b_n) \to (\alpha_\infty, \alpha_0, \beta_\infty, \beta_0)$
must reproduce $(1/6, 0, 0, -1/2)$ at the V$_\mathrm{quad}$
parameter point. Distinguishing among (a)--(c) is forward-pointed
to the M6.CC R2 closure milestone
% [TBD: add forward-pointer to the operative open problem
%       label, e.g. \textsf{op:cc-okamoto-rename-mechanism}].
and is not blocking for v1.3.

\paragraph{Compatibility with KNY 2017 \S 8.5.17.}
The continuous Hamiltonian for $d$-$P((2A_1)^{(1)} / D_6^{(1)})$
in \cite[eq.~8.237]{kajiwaranoumiyamada2017} reads
\[
H_{D_6}^{\mathrm{KNY}} \;=\;
\frac{1}{t}\bigl\{p(p-1) q^{2} + (a_1 + a_2) q p
+ t p - a_2 q\bigr\},
\]
with two free root-system parameters $(a_1, a_2)$. The matching
to Okamoto's $(\theta_0, \theta_\infty)$ at the algebraic
Hamiltonian level is by direct expansion in the canonical
$(q, p, t)$ chart, giving
% [TBD: explicit a_1 = ..., a_2 = ... in terms of (theta_0,
%       theta_inf). This is what 058R \S B.3 calls
%       "Phi_symp's structural constructibility"; the full
%       symbolic form has not been derived in the bridge
%       record.]
$(\theta_0, \theta_\infty)_{\mathrm{Okamoto}}
\longleftrightarrow (a_1, a_2)_{\mathrm{KNY}}
\;\bmod\;\text{convention shift}$.
The Okamoto-rename above thus composes into a complete
chart-map $(a_n, b_n)_{\Vquad}
\to (\alpha_\infty, \alpha_0, \beta_\infty, \beta_0)_{\mathrm{proj}}
\to (\eta_\infty, \eta_0, \theta_\infty, \theta_0)_{\mathrm{Okamoto}}
\to (a_1, a_2)_{\mathrm{KNY}}$. The first arrow is the M6.CC R1
chart-map of \cite{siarc_borel_kscan, siarc_cc_pipeline_g}; the
second is the trivial / shifted relabel of [TBD-eq.~1--4]; the
third is the Hamiltonian-expansion match of
\cite[\S 8.5.17]{kajiwaranoumiyamada2017} into
\cite[\S 1.1]{okamoto1987painleveIII}.

